2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed technique combines counterexample-guided inductive synthesis with a novel inductive synthesis algorithm, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 

3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper deals with relational program synthesis, which involves reasoning about logical relations between programs. 

4. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The proposed technique can be used for automated program inversion and automatic generation of comparators, which are important problems in software engineering. 

5. cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper deals with synthesizing string encoders/decoders, which involves formal languages and automata theory.
